&quot;It's funny to hear skalds whine about minstrels and minstrels whine about skalds. 2 uber classes whining about the other uber class, lol. &quot;<br>
<br>
Always makes me laugh to see people whining about people &quot;whining&quot;. Especially as the person making the comments about the &quot;whining&quot; usually has no reason to even be on the board, thus making them comming from a more whiney stand point then a genuinely constructive one. But there you go. Neither of those classes are uber. Unless of course you define uber as &quot;works well&quot; in which case you'd probably have everyone in the game playing at Spiritmaster and Shaman capability before your happy. Sheesh.<br>
<br>
Simple lesson for you - Skalds, Minstrels, Bards are all covetous of each others classes, because they all appear at first glance similar, yet end up very different. Each of the classes would love to keep their own strengths and have the other ones strengths too. Now that would be uber, but it isn't going to happen. It's just a natural human thing to feel. A lot of people take up one class thinking they will play more like one of the others.<br>
<br>
And it peeves me off how on a Skald board there are clearly so many non skalds here just to whine. That is sad<br>
<br>
&quot;SoS does not increase run speed more than the top run song does! Please, get the facts straight before you whine about something. &quot;<br>
