<br>
&quot;You can always tell when someone's making a relic play because they start taking your forts.&quot;<br>
<br>
WRONG. Since Darkness Falls you can't tell a relic raid anymore by when they &quot;start taking your forts&quot;, you only know when they've taken at least half of your forts.  Quite regularly a realm will come in and take around 3 forts before heading back to find a df group.<br>
<br>
Okay now a point on minstrels. Minstrels are a flexible and strong class, but they are also complex and hard to play. If you list their abilities off, of course they sound uber, but they easy thing to miss (especially if you've never played one) is they can't use all their abilities at once. If they are stealthed they can't sing, or charm. If they have a pet they can't stealth (pulsing effect), or sing (because the charm is a vocal song itself), until recently they couldn't fight either as they had to use a flute to charm. Finally if they have the drums out for the normal speed song, they can't fight, have a pet or stealth. <br>
<br>
You need to be very sneaky and tactical to use a minstrel well. *That* and that alone is why minstrels are fewer then skalds. As much as I love skalds, it has to be said it is a very straight forward class.<br>
<br>
However the general power of skalds and minstrels is TOTALLY IRRELEVENT, when the only issue that this thread is about is the SoS song. And you only need to read minstrel forums to see that EVERY MINSTREL IN THE GAME wants this ability. So if that is not an uber ability, I do not know what is.<br>
<br>
The speed of it is fairly irrelevent too, the uberness is in the fact it is total mez/stun/snare resistance (okay you can't attack, but you can't be frozen) for your entier group for 30 seconds. Even without the speed that'd be uber, especially as it only costs 10 rsp, the *same* as a simple purge, and 4 points cheaper then the skald realm skill which is a fairly weak dmg add.<br>
<br>
I am wondering if you can even use this after you've been stuned/mezed/rooted to get out of it. That is something that you really shouldn't be able to do (especially stun/mezed) but I suspect you can.<br>
<br>
I actually think they set the price before they added the mez/stun/snare protection. As it stands at the moment I'd start by swapping the cost of SoS and FoG, then improve the damage for FoG and put a limiter like has been suggested to stop multiple SoS abuse. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/12/02 9:09:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Realm abilities</span><hr size=1> IMHO, Realm Abilities shouldn't be part of class balance, and taken into account in that regard. Class should be balanced without needing to spend a single realm ability point, and it shouldn't require you to take so and so realm ability to fix a weak hole in your class. Realm Abilities shoud be &quot;nice to have&quot; abilities, that actively or passively add to your global efficiency without beeing class defining by themselves. <br>
If you add realm abilities that have a non trivial influence on how you play your class in RvR, give it to everyone, which is the case with, for exemple, purge and ignore pain.<br>
<br>
What I hate with RA is that some classes have been given killer, must have abilities and the others junk. If you are weighing whether you are going to take your class specific abiltiy or another one (serenity, purge, mastery of pain, anything), it means Mythic are right on the target. <br>
If you are taking at top priority your &quot;must abosolutely have&quot; class ability (like SoS), it's wrong. If you'll never admit openly you took by lack of information your class ability and discretly respec it, pretending it never happened, it's wrong. Unfortunately, it's the case with Fury of the Gods.<br>
<br>
It has nothing to do with the relative strength of Minstrels and Skalds. <br>
<br>
Dargaard, skald of Guenievre <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/12/02 11:21:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realm abilities</span><hr size=1> I agree totally about the class balance. It's something I've been hassling mythic about since RA's came out (not got any response). It seems to me there are three parts of each class, the class itself, spice abilitys (3 were added to the game and then they seem to have been abandoned), and realm abilities and they should all be balananced indervidually as seperate entities. There are too many &quot;make up for weakness&quot; realm abilities (like a lot of the pure tanks ones). <br>
<br>
The worst realm ability for me is the war cry AE taunt one. How can they possibly say that a clearly PvE only ability should be a reward for collecting up points for doing RvR. I thought the whole point of RA's was to reward you in RvR for doing RvR. The they made it very expensive and have expensive pre-reqs. That beats the fast swim one hands down imho (at least you only have to waste 1 pt on it to try it out). A pb ae taunt should have been a warrior (and similar) ability in their basic skills from day one.<br>
<br>
But anyway, that's off the skaldic topic so I'll stop ranting.<br>
<br>
Realm abilities seem to have been rushed in without proper planning, and in such a way that making changes will be difficult (we've already seen people get bonus points by purchasing abilities that then became more expensive, while others have been forced to respec or loose points because what they spent points on became cheaper). In the case of FoG, seeing as no one has it (since respec) that wouldn't be so much of an issue. Younger minstrels would be up in arms if SoS was made more expensive though (as the older ones would have it for the old price), so maybe decreasing costs is better then increasing (at least until you run out of re-specs, which basically means to me they need to do all the RA changes *at once* for minimal complication).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/12/02 12:03:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realm abilities</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately, they are using realm abilities to balance classes. See Hidden is a perfect example.<br>
<br>
I guess I shouldn't come here and whine about skalds whining, since I only play a lvl 40.5 skald. I guess I shouldn't whine about minstrels whining either (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=30841821&replies=126">vnboards.ign.com/message....eplies=126</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->   pages 3+, my name is Esoa_of_Hatred), because I only play a lvl 50 minstrel. Geez. <br>
<br>
As for skalds/minstrels being uber, I was exaggerating. They are, however, much much better than many other classes and clearly in the top 5. All classes, like it or not, should be reasonably equal. That doesn't mean that some won't be better, it means that there won't be the huge gap between classes like skalds/minstrels/clerics and classes like spiritmasters/cabalists/shaman.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think that all 3 realms should get this ability. I think a lot of realm abilities need to be looked at because they are overpriced and underpowered, or the other way around. Albion certainly got much better RA's than the other realms, and SoS is certainly better than the skald RA (cheaper too). It clearly has issues. However, I think it should stay as long as the exploit possibilities are fixed.<br>
<br>
