 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udaocobserver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DAoC Observer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 4:30:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> It is very stupid for an ability as powerful as a speed doubler to be uninterruptible and uncounterable by any means. Speed = invincibility and everyone knows it. And everyone seems to have this blindness about the possibility of a relic raiding group having, gasp, more than one Minstrel with SoS. Hard to imagine how that will ever happen, granting that only 99% of all Minstrels are likely to buy that ability, isn't it?<br>
